cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with identifying communities of users on social media platforms like Twitter and Facebook. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a novel approach to tackle the challenge of identifying coherent topic-dependent user groups. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper deals with social media and user interactions. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with recommending content to users based on their interests. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing and analyzing text data from social media platforms.
